Text.Value: Get moving. If I see you slavers again, I'll tear you apart.
Your brain going mushy, jargh? That's where those Absolute-freaks hole up.
Gnomes walk. Or you DIE.
The gnomes go free, and you get to live. Everybody wins.
Psh. I'll let you keep breathin', and we'll call things square.
Clan: grab your gear, wipe your arses.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.logicalname: at least one other rebel still alive.

Text.Value: You've got this backwards. You keep your head, and I pay you nothing.
Understood. I won't interfere.
Take me on, and you'll look like a fool. Walk away, and you save face.
Good doing business with you.
Won't hear me argue. Your mouth's got the might to back it.
I killed Nere for you. That's payment enough.
Try it, ya uppity shit, see what happens.
My gods. What in all Nine Hells is wrong with you?!
I've reconsidered our deal, Brithvar. Free the slaves, or this place becomes your tomb.
Shit - I've seen this jargh fight. Drugnin' animal. But sooner die than lose face.
Gnome-pricks: you're off the hook. Scram, before I get my senses.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general
EditorData.NodeContext: Addressed to the room in general

Text.Value: Clan property. They come with us.
Hardly. They drag their feet, and I'll scorch their arses. Works every time.
Deal's off, jargh. I told you to squish that floatin' eyeball. Now the damn thing's seen us put Nere down.
Leave.
And the slaves? What about them?

EditorData.logicalname: At least one gnome still alive

Text.Value: Have you no heart? They deserved freedom - and you denied it.
Read the duergar's mind.
You rakkah. Good thing you ain't one of mine - I'd be sliding a cane up your hole and twisting.
Set them free, or I will thrash you like I thrashed Nere.
I am freeing these gnomes. Just try and stop me.
Your wish is my command, jargh.
Drugnin' jargh. Have it your way.
Born to serve, my father said. I'll keep 'em busy.
Drugh. Fine. Besides, we got shit to do. Gold ain't gonna hoard itself.
We had a deal. You owe me, not the other way around.

EditorData.logicalname: Gave quest to kill eye but player failed

Text.Value: That was the wrong answer. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Zavagh! is a battle cry. za-VAHG!

Text.Value: You are going to gut ME? HAH.
Gut me? Try it - doubt you'll even pierce skin.
Restitution, my arse. You'll find what you need on Nere's corpse.
Thanks to you, we got a cult-army on our tail. Now pay up - or I bleed you dry.
Mm. For a jargh, you got smarts.
I wasn't asking. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Zavagh! is a battle cry. za-VAHG!

Text.Value: You messing in heads? I won't stand for that shit. Zavagh!
Good idea. They're a valuable asset.
Now lug your arse someplace else - I got to get cracking.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to the room in general.

Text.Value: Mm - you got a point. Likely to be all hobbled up, what with the lashings.
Please. We catch your scent, and you'll get sliced 'fore you can bat your left eye.
Let the gnomes go. They'll just slow you down.
What makes Moonrise Towers such a threat?
I don't have that kind of gold on me.
Pay up, and you get to slink away. Resist, and I gut you. ([6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
The way I hear tell, some prick there calls the shots. The General, Nere called him.
Drop it. I don't owe you anything.
Then do it, ya shit. We'll see who thrashes who.
Goblins, drow, gnolls, even humans - ain't no one they won't try to turn. They've gathered a damned army.
That so? Then your head should do nicely. Zavagh!

EditorData.NodeContext: Zavagh! is a battle cry. za-VAHG!

Text.Value: Listen, coward. We had an agreement, and I don't take kindly to oathbreakers.
Pft. Sure, they can take the gnomes. Over our dead bodies. Right?
Time I scrammed before more pricks from Moonrise Towers move in.
Freeze it, cock-stench. We aren't done just yet.
The gnomes should be able to go where they please. They are not the duergar's to keep.
Speak up, chief. You can't just let the clan keep them.
And there ain't no way I'm sticking around long enough to meet him.
Nere and his Absolute wanks owed us a wad of coin. And the dregs on his corpse aren't gonna cut it.
You've got this all wrong. I pay you nothing, and you keep your head.
Brittle are the foundations upon which the houses of tyrants are built. It seems I judged you to be less brittle than you really are.

Synopsis: In this dialogue, you have killed Nere without doing the duergar mutineers quest. As a result, they want you to pay for the trouble you've caused. You can give them money, persuade them to let you live, or attack.
